annotationA: Nascent polypeptide-associated complex subunit alpha; May promote appropriate targeting of ribosome-nascent polypeptide complexes (By similarity). Required for correct localization of the osk/oskar protein to the posterior pole during embryonic development. The osk protein directs the recruitment of molecules responsible for posterior body patterning and germline formation in the embryo
annotationB: 60S ribosomal protein L31; Structural constituent of ribosome. It is involved in the biological process described with: mitotic spindle elongation; translation; mitotic spindle organization; Belongs to the eukaryotic ribosomal protein eL31 family
